column1: # Name: Government spending on education as a % of GDP

# Definition: Public expenditure on education as % of GDP is the total public expenditure (current and capital) on education expressed as a percentage of the Gross Domestic Product (GDP) in a given year. Public expenditure on education includes government spending on educational institutions (both public and private), education administration, and transfers/subsidies for private entities (students/households and other privates entities).
# Data from the No Ceilings project: http://noceilings.org
# For more about the data, please visit http://noceilings.org/data
